A breadth-first search can be easily handled with recursion (in fact, I'd argue the specification is almost as simple):<p><pre><code>  def bfs(search_node, nodes_to_visit):
      node = nodes_to_visit.pop()
      if node == search_node:
          return node
      else:
          nodes_to_visit.extend(node.neighbors)
          return bfs(search_node, nodes_to_visit)

  bfs(search_node, [root_node])</code></pre>
